    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to members of several families in different superfamilies of insects in the suborder Apocrita having in common that they have the abdomen attached to the thorax by a slender petiole or waist, most are winged, and the females have a stinger.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
